ttom of the concept of "environment" in the world religions. How do religions position themselves on the ecological question? What are the foundations of their decisions? And can they make a significant contribution to the current problem and to the enquiries of many people?  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aInterreligiöser Dialog. 4aSchöpfung. 4aUmweltethik. 4aÖkologie.  aInterreligious dialogue.  aLaudato si.  acreation.  aecology.1 aBöttigheimer, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöttigheimer, Christoph, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDee, Rabbi Leo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDutton, Yasin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeril, Rabbi Yonatan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchlögl-Flierl, Kerstin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWidenka, Wenzel M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWidenka, Wenzel Maximilian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cEPUBz97831107826910 cprintz978311078231840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311078245540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110782455423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110782455/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK